    scene bg ch13_4001e7_25 at full_bg
    "You both look out over the black water. The town below is a scatter of small lights and louder claims. The exposure you forced today has changed the calculus: the municipal attorneys will meet, Cassandra 'Cass'"
    "Whitlock's legal team will mobilize, relocations will be drafted faster under the new scrutiny, and the whistleblower—Harper Kline—remains absent, sacrificed to safety."
    "You let yourself feel the very negative shape of it: moral clarity that cuts like glass, rippling into lives and homes. The arousal—the panic, the urgent legal and social machinery—rushes toward you like an incoming tide."
    "You breathe. You taste iron and salt and the raw edge of what you have chosen."

